n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-237" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution">
<ol class=3D"lower-alpha">
<li id=3D"li-568">
<p id=3D"p-1865">The marginal cost \(C'\) is given by the derivative of the=
 total cost function \(C\text{.}\) Thus,</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} C'(q) \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{C(q+h)-C(q)}{h}\\ \amp =
=3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{0.0001(q+h)^{3} -0.08(q+h)^{2}+40(q+h)+5000-0.001q=
^{3}+0.08q^{2}-40q-5000}{h} \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1865-part2">We expand, combine like-terms, and simplify by \(h\)=
 to find</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
C'(q) =3D 0.003q^{2}-0.16q+40\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-569">
<p id=3D"p-1866">The marginal cost when \(q =3D 200,300,400\text{,}\) and \=
(600\) is given by</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} \amp C'(200)=3D0.003(200)^{2}-0.16(200)+40=3D20\\ \amp C'(300=
)=3D0.003(300)^{2}-0.16(300)+40=3D19\\ \amp C'(400)=3D0.003(400)^{2}-0.16(4=
00)+40=3D24\\ \amp C'(600)=3D0.003(600)^{2}-0.16(600)+40=3D52 \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1866-part2">or $\(20\text{,}\) $\(19\text{,}\) $\(24\) and $\(52=
\text{,}\) respectively.</p>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-570"><p id=3D"p-1867">We deduce from part (b) that the manufac=
turer's actual cost for producing the 201st tactical flashlight is approxim=
ated by $20. Similarly, the approximated cost is $19 for the 301st tactical=
 flashlight, and so on. We also notice that when the level of production is=
 already 600 units, the actual cost of producing one additional unit is app=
roximately $52. This increase in cost may be the result of several factors,=
 among them excessive costs incurred because of higher maintenance, overtim=
e to keep up with demand, production breakdown due to greater stress and st=
rain on the equipment, and so on. Below, the graph of the total cost functi=
on is shown with \(C(q)\) measured in thousands of dollars.</p></li>
</ol>
