<li id=3D"li-574">
<p id=3D"p-1873">We determine the revenue function \(R\) to be</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} R(q) \amp =3D pq \\ \amp =3D q(-0.02q + 400)\\ \amp =3D -0.02=
q^{2}+400q \ \ \ 0\leq q \leq 20,000 \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-575">
<p id=3D"p-1874">We determine the marginal revenue function \(R'\) to be</p=
>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split}
R'(q) \amp=3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{R(q+h)-R(q)}{h}\\ \amp=3D \lim_{h\to 0} =
\dfrac{-0.02(q+h)^{2}+400(q+h)+0.02q^{2}-400q}{h}\end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1874-part2">We expand and simplify:</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} R'(q) \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{-0.02(q^{2}+2qh+h^{2})+40=
0q+400h+0.02q^{2}-400q}{h} \\ \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{-0.04qh -0.02h^=
{2}+400h}{h}\\ \amp =3D\lim_{h\to 0} \left(-0.04q-0.02h^{2}+400\right)\\ \a=
mp =3D -0.04q + 400 \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-576"><p id=3D"p-1875">\(R'(2000) =3D -0.04(2000)+400 =3D 320\t=
ext{.}\) Therefore, the actual revenue from selling the 2001st product is a=
pproximated by $320.</p></li>
</ol></div></div>
