<li id=3D"li-581">
<p id=3D"p-1881">From part (a) of <a data-knowl=3D"./knowl/exa_Marginal_Rev=
enue_Function.html" title=3D"Example 4.20: Marginal Revenue Function" href=
=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20Notes/sec_The=
DerivativeFunction.html">example&nbsp;4.20</a>, we have</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
R(q)=3D -0.02q^{2}+400q\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1881-part2">Hence, we determine the profit function \(P\) to be<=
/p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} P(q) \amp =3D R(q) - C(q) \\ \amp =3D \left(-0.02q^{2}+400q\r=
ight) - \left(100q+200,000\right)\\ \amp =3D-0.02q^{2} + 300q - 200,000 \en=
d{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-582">
<p id=3D"p-1882">The marginal profit function \(P'\) is given by</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} P'(q) \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{P(q+h)-P(q)}{h} \\ \amp =
=3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{-0.02(q+h)^{2}+300(q+h)-200,000+0.02q^{2}-300q+200=
,000}{h} \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1882-part2">As above, we expand and simplify to find</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
P'(q) =3D -0.04q + 300\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-583"><p id=3D"p-1883">\(P'(2000)=3D-0.04(2000)+300=3D220\text{=
.}\) Therefore, the actual profit from selling the 2001st product is approx=
imated by $220</p></li>
