n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-240" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution">
<ol class=3D"lower-alpha">
<li id=3D"li-589">
<p id=3D"p-1891">From the definition of the derivative, we have</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split}
I'(t) \amp=3D \lim_{h \to 0} \dfrac{I(t+h)-I(t)}{h}\\ \amp=3D \lim_{h \to 0=
} \dfrac{-0.2(t+h)^{3}+3(t+h)^{2}+100 +0.2t^{3}-3t^{2}-100}{h}\end{split}\t=
ext{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1891-part2">We expand, group like-terms, and simplify by \(h\) t=
o find</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
I'(t) =3D \lim_{h \to 0} \left(-0.6t^{2}-0.2h^{2}-0.6ht + 6t +3h\right)=3D =
-0.6t^{2}+6t\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-590">
<p id=3D"p-1892">We compute</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\
I'(6) =3D -0.6(6)^{2} + 6)6) =3D 14.4, \ \ \text{ and }=20
\end{equation*}
</div>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
I(6) =3D -0.2(6)^{3}+3(6)^{2} + 100 =3D 164.8
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1892-part2">From which we see that the inflation rate is</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\dfrac{I'(6)}{I(6)} =3D \dfrac{14.4}{164.8} \simeq 0.0874
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1892-part3">or approximately \(8.7\) percent.</p>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-591">
<p id=3D"p-1893">We must now compute</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
I''(t) =3D \lim_{h \to 0} \dfrac{I'(t+h)-I'(t)}{h}\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1893-part2">Using the above result, we get</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
I''(t) =3D \lim_{h \to 0} \dfrac{(0.6(t+h)^{2}+6(t+h))-(-0.6t^{2} + 6t)}{h}=
\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1893-part3">We again expand, simplify and take the limit to find=
</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
I''(t) =3D -1.2t+6\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-592">
<p id=3D"p-1894">Since</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
I''(6) =3D -1.2(6) + 6 =3D -1.2\text{,}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1894-part2">we see that \(I'\) is indeed decreasing at \(t =3D 6=
\) and conclude that inflation was levelling off at the time (see figures b=
elow).</p>
</li>
</ol>
