<li id=3D"li-593">
<p id=3D"p-1903">\(\ds f(x)=3D\sqrt{169-x^2}\)</p>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-answer-309" id=3D"answ=
er-309" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20N=
otes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Answer</span></a>=
<div id=3D"hk-answer-309" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><div clas=
s=3D"solution">\(\ds -x/\sqrt{169-x^2}\)</div></div>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-solution-242" id=3D"so=
lution-242" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course=
%20Notes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Solution</spa=
n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-242" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution">
<p id=3D"p-1904">We find the derivative \(f'(x)\) of \(f(x) =3D \sqrt{169-x=
^{2}}\) using the definition of the derivative.</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} f'(x) \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \ \dfrac{\sqrt{169-(x+h)^{2}}-\s=
qrt{169-x^{2}}}{h} \\  \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \ \frac{1}{h} \cdot \dfrac{\l=
eft(\sqrt{169-(x+h)^{2}}-\sqrt{169-x^{2}}\right)\left(\sqrt{169-(x+h)^{2}}+=
\sqrt{169-x^{2}}\right)}{\sqrt{169-(x+h)^{2}}+\sqrt{169-x^{2}}} .\end{split=
}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1904-part2">Simplifying the above expression gives</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} f'(x) \amp =3D \lim_{h \to 0} \ \frac{1}{h} \cdot \dfrac{-h(h=
+2x)}{\sqrt{169-(x+h)^{2}}+\sqrt{169-x^{2}}} \\ \amp =3D \lim_{h \to 0} \ \=
dfrac{-(h+2x)}{\sqrt{169-(x+h)^{2}} + \sqrt{169-x^{2}}} \\  \amp =3D \dfrac=
{-x}{\sqrt{169-x^{2}}} \cdot \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</div></div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-594">
<p id=3D"p-1905">\(\ds h(t)=3D80-4.9t^2\)</p>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-answer-310" id=3D"answ=
er-310" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20N=
otes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Answer</span></a>=
<div id=3D"hk-answer-310" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><div clas=
s=3D"solution">\(\ds -9.8t\)</div></div>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-solution-243" id=3D"so=
lution-243" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course=
%20Notes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Solution</spa=
n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-243" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution"><p id=3D"p-1906">\(\begin{aligned}h'(t) \amp =3D \li=
m\limits_{k\to 0} \dfrac{h(t+k)-h(t)}{k}\\ \amp =3D \lim\limits_{k\to 0} \d=
frac{80-4.9(t+k)^2-80+4.9t^2}{k}\\ \amp =3D \lim\limits_{k\to 0} \dfrac{-4.=
9(t^2+2tk+k^2) + 4.9t^2}{k}\\ \amp =3D \lim\limits_{k\to 0} \dfrac{-4.9(2tk=
+k^2)}{k} \\ \amp =3D \lim\limits_{k\to 0} -4.9(2t+k) =3D -9.8t \end{aligne=
d}\)</p></div></div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-595">
<p id=3D"p-1907">\(\ds g(x)=3Dx^2-(1/x)\)</p>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-answer-311" id=3D"answ=
er-311" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20N=
otes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Answer</span></a>=
<div id=3D"hk-answer-311" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><div clas=
s=3D"solution">\(\ds 2x+1/x^2\)</div></div>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-solution-244" id=3D"so=
lution-244" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course=
%20Notes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Solution</spa=
n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-244" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution"><p id=3D"p-1908">\(\begin{aligned}g'(x) \amp =3D \li=
m\limits_{h \to 0} \dfrac{g(x+h)-g(x)}{h}\\ \amp =3D\lim\limits_{h \to 0} \=
dfrac{\left((x+h)^2-\frac{1}{x+h}\right) - \left(x^2-\frac{1}{x}\right)}{h}=
 \\ \amp =3D\lim\limits_{h \to 0} \frac{ x^2 + 2xh + h^2 - x^2 - \frac{1}{x=
+h} + \frac{1}{x} } {h}\\ \amp =3D\lim\limits_{h \to 0} \frac{2xh + h^2 + \=
frac{-x + x + h}{x(x+h)}}{h}\\ \amp =3D\lim\limits_{h \to 0} \left(2x + h +=
 \frac{1}{x(x+h)}\right)\\ \amp =3D 2x + \frac{1}{x^2} \end{aligned}\)</p><=
/div></div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-596">
<p id=3D"p-1909">\(\ds f(x)=3Dax^2+bx+c\text{,}\) where \(a\text{,}\) \(b\t=
ext{,}\) and \(c\) are constants.</p>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-answer-312" id=3D"answ=
er-312" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20N=
otes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Answer</span></a>=
<div id=3D"hk-answer-312" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><div clas=
s=3D"solution">\(\ds 2ax+b\)</div></div>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-solution-245" id=3D"so=
lution-245" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course=
%20Notes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Solution</spa=
n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-245" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution">
<p id=3D"p-1910">Let \(f(x) =3D ax^{2}+bx+c\) for any constants \(a,b,c\tex=
t{.}\) We take the derivative with respect to \(x\text{,}\)</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\diff{f}{x}=3D f'(x) =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \dfrac{a(x+h)^{2}+b(x+h)+c-ax^{2}-bx=
-c}{h} \cdot
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1910-part2">Expand \(a(x+h)^{2}\) and \(b(x+h)\) and notice the =
terms which cancel. We find</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} f'(x) \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \ \dfrac{2axh+ah^{2}+bh}{h}   \a=
mp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \ \dfrac{2axh+ah^{2}+bh}{h}   \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \=
 \left(2ax+ah+b\right)   \amp =3D 2ax+b. \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p id=3D"p-1910-part3">And so we find that  \(\diff{}{x} \left(ax^{2}+bx+c\=
right) =3D 2ax + b\text{.}\)</p>
</div></div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-597">
<p id=3D"p-1911">\(\ds h(x)=3Dx^3\)</p>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-answer-313" id=3D"answ=
er-313" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20N=
otes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Answer</span></a>=
<div id=3D"hk-answer-313" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><div clas=
s=3D"solution">\(\ds 3x^2\)</div></div>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-solution-246" id=3D"so=
lution-246" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course=
%20Notes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Solution</spa=
n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-246" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution"><p id=3D"p-1912">\(\begin{aligned}h'(x) \amp =3D \li=
m\limits_{k \to 0} \frac{h(x+k)-h(x)}{k} \\ \amp =3D \lim\limits_{h \to 0} =
\frac{(x+k)^3 - x^3}{h}\\ \amp =3D\lim\limits_{h \to 0} \frac{ x^3 +3x^2k +=
 3xk^2 + k^3 - x^3}{k}\\ \amp =3D\lim\limits_{h \to 0} \frac{3x^2k + 2xk^2}=
{k}\\ \amp =3D\lim\limits_{h \to 0} \left(3x^2+2xk\right)\\ \amp =3D 3x^2 \=
end{aligned}\)</p></div></div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-598">
<p id=3D"p-1913">\(\ds f(t)=3D2/\sqrt{2t+1}\)</p>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-answer-314" id=3D"answ=
er-314" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20N=
otes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Answer</span></a>=
<div id=3D"hk-answer-314" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><div clas=
s=3D"solution">\(\ds -2/(2t+1)^{3/2}\)</div></div>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-solution-247" id=3D"so=
lution-247" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course=
%20Notes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Solution</spa=
n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-247" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution"><p id=3D"p-1914">\(\begin{aligned}f'(t) \amp =3D \li=
m\limits_{h\to 0} \dfrac{f(t+h)-f(t)}{h} \\ \amp =3D \lim\limits_{h\to 0} \=
dfrac{\frac{2}{\sqrt{2(t+h)+1}}-\frac{2}{\sqrt{2t+1}}}{h}\\ \amp =3D 2\lim\=
limits_{h\to 0} \dfrac{1}{h} \cdot \left(\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2(t+h)+1}}-\dfrac{=
1}{\sqrt{2t+1}}\right)\\ \amp =3D 2\lim\limits_{h\to 0} \dfrac{1}{h} \cdot =
\left(\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2(t+h)+1}}-\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2t+1}}\right) \cdot \left(=
\dfrac{\frac{1}{\sqrt{2(t+h)+1}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{2t+1}}}{\frac{1}{\sqrt{2(t+=
h)+1}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{2t+1}}}\right)\\ \amp =3D 2\lim\limits_{h\to 0} \dfra=
c{1}{h} \cdot \left(\frac{-2h}{(2t+1)(2h+2t+1)}\right) \cdot \left(\dfrac{1=
}{\frac{1}{\sqrt{2(t+h)+1}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{2t+1}}}\right)\\ \amp =3D 2\lim\=
limits_{h\to 0} \left(\frac{-2}{(2t+1)(2h+2t+1)}\right) \cdot \left(\dfrac{=
1}{\frac{1}{\sqrt{2(t+h)+1}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{2t+1}}}\right)\\ \amp =3D 2 \cd=
ot \left(\frac{-2}{(2t+1)(2t+1)}\right) \cdot \left(\dfrac{1}{\frac{1}{\sqr=
t{2t+1}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{2t+1}}}\right)\\ \amp =3D2 \cdot \left(\frac{-2}{(2=
t+1)^2 \cdot 2(2t+1)^{-1/2}}\right) =3D \dfrac{-2}{(2t+1)^{3/2}}. \end{alig=
ned}\)</p></div></div>
</li>
<li id=3D"li-599">
<p id=3D"p-1915">\(\ds g(t)=3D(2t-1)/(t+2)\)</p>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-answer-315" id=3D"answ=
er-315" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course%20N=
otes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Answer</span></a>=
<div id=3D"hk-answer-315" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><div clas=
s=3D"solution">\(\ds 5/(t+2)^2\)</div></div>
<a data-knowl=3D"" class=3D"id-ref" data-refid=3D"hk-solution-248" id=3D"so=
lution-248" href=3D"https://www.sfu.ca/math-coursenotes/Math%20157%20Course=
%20Notes/sec_TheDerivativeFunction.html"><span class=3D"type">Solution</spa=
n></a><div id=3D"hk-solution-248" class=3D"hidden-content tex2jax_ignore"><=
div class=3D"solution">
<p id=3D"p-1916">Now, we consider the function \(g(t)=3D\dfrac{2t-1}{t+2}\)=
 and take the derivative with respect to \(t\text{.}\)</p>
<div class=3D"displaymath">
\begin{equation*}
\begin{split} \diff{g}{t} =3D g'(t) \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \ \frac{1}{h} \c=
dot \left(\dfrac{2(t+h)-1}{(t+h)+2}-\dfrac{2t-1}{t+2}\right) \\  \amp =3D \=
lim_{h\to 0} \ \frac{1}{h} \cdot \dfrac{(2t+2h-1)(t+2) - (2t-1)(t+2+h)}{(t+=
2)(t+h+2)} \\  \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \ \frac{1}{h} \cdot \dfrac{5h}{(t+2)(=
t+h+2)}  \\ \amp =3D \lim_{h\to 0} \ \dfrac{5}{(t+2)(t+h+2)} \\  \amp =3D \=
dfrac{5}{(t+2)^{2}} \cdot \end{split}
\end{equation*}
</div>
</div></div>
</li>
</ol></article></div>
